We restated our recommendation, and Management agreed to:

Issue a memorandum order enjoining all officers and employees of the municipality to strictly comply with Section 89 of PD No. 1445 and item 5 of COA Circular 97-002, with a demand to all those who have outstanding CAs to liquidate immediately;

For past due Cash advances ageing more than 10 years, instruct the accounting office to review the probability of collection and if remote, issue a duly substantiated request for write-off of dormant accounts receivables in accordance with COA Circular No. 2023-008;

Instruct the accounting office to evaluate the records for unpaid claims of deceased officers and employees for possible application to their existing liabilities;

Demand those employees who transferred from, or are no longer connected with the municipality, and request assistance to the agency they are currently connected with for the collection of the accountable officers’ outstanding Cash advances; and

Require the Municipal Accountant to provide a certification that the previous CA is already settled or liquidated on the face of the DVs for Cash advances.

We recommended, and Management agreed to require the GFPS to:

Update the GAD Database to contain gender analysis identifying gender issues and determine gender-responsive PPAs for prioritization in programming and budgeting in the annual GPB in accordance with Annex B of PCW-DILG-DBM-NEDA JMC No.2013-01;

Prepare the LGU GAD Agenda for the remaining term of the LCE based on the results of gender analysis conducted on the GAD Database and/or any other gender analysis tools;

Prepare the annual GPB in accordance with the provisions of PCW-DILG-DBM-NEDA JMC No.2013-01, as amended by JMC No.2016-01 and include priority gender issues identified in the GAD Agenda; and

Undergo seminars and training to equip them with proper knowledge to effectively implement the GAD concepts, processes, rules and regulations.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive:

Issue a memorandum order: a. Requiring the responsible offices to fund transfer to the bank account of the 20% Development Fund the share in the CY 2022 IRA which were not transferred;

Constituting a committee with representatives from the accounting, treasury, and budget offices, for the purpose of reconciling the three offices’ respective balances of the 20% DF;

Require the committee to furnish to the audit team the result of the reconciliation, including the working papers thereof.

The Municipal Mayor to:

Direct the Municipal Engineering Office to prepare and maintain a monthly monitoring report to keep track of the progress of all PPAs specially those that involved infrastructure projects within its jurisdiction from planning to its completion stage;

Assign Project Heads/Managers to all non-infrastructure PPAs to prepare and consolidate a Monthly Monitoring Report;

Direct the Municipal Engineering Office and the assigned Project Heads/Managers to coordinate with the Municipal Accountant on the costs incurred in each PPAs as basis in the preparation of their Monthly Monitoring Report which should be submitted to COA at least on a quarterly basis; and

Require the Municipal Engineering Office and the assigned Project Heads/Manager to strictly adhere to the provisions of COA Circular No. 2013-004.

To strengthen the risk management capabilities of the Municipal Government and enable it to manage its vulnerabilities in the event of disruptive events, the LCE institutionalize the PSCP by creating a working group that will perform the following activities:

•to conduct risk assessment; 
•to identify critical processes and functions; 
•to determine scenarios that may disrupt normal operation; 
•to conduct risk analysis and impact analysis; 
•to formulate the PSCP based on the identified risks on critical processes and functions and its related steps to be followed to eliminate, if not mitigate, the impact of the determined disruptions following the prescribed template and be guided by the PSCP guidebook; and
•to submit plan to the MDRRMO for review, to the LCE for approval, and to the Sangguniang Bayan for the passage of a resolution to institutionalize the PSCP.

Management should improve their monitoring of operational requirements like the submission of PSCP.

