D. After liquidation of cash advance, a copy of the transmittal letter duly received by the ICFAU should be forwarded to the COA ATL concerned notwithstanding to the cash advance to be made during the quarter. Responsibilities of the Agency Accountant and the HoA on the granting and liquidation of CF should be religiously adhered to and should be in accordance with the provisions of COA-DBM-DILG-GCG-DND Joint Circular No. 2015-01 and other applicable laws.

In view of the foregoing, we recommend that management shall:

create a team to immediately and without delay, conduct a thorough investigation and analysis of prior years’ transactions in order to establish the causes of the discrepancy, which could be errors in recording and/or cash shortage of the accountable officers;

direct concerned officers and employees of the Treasury and Accounting Offices to exercise prudence in recording financial transactions and perform reconciliation procedures on a periodic basis to prevent the accumulation of unreconciled balances;

ensure that proper review of recorded transactions is done by concerned officers of the Accounting Unit as a deterrent to errors and irregularities; and

disclose in the financial statements the above-mentioned discrepancy and the action taken by management pending final resolution or outcome of the investigation.

